# SPPARKS App "potts"

# This group of apps run the standard potts model dynamics, using either the 
# Metropolis algorithm (sweeping) or KMC. Apart from subtle effects, such as 
# wild spins (KMC does not allow them), 
# the various methods give equivalent results, if delt for 
# Metroplis sweeping is set to 1/Ns 
#
# app_style	lat Nx Ny (Nz) Ns 12345 (random) (read filename)
#  		    = lattice of type lat and size Nx by Ny (by Nz), Ns = spins, RN
#		lat = potts/2d/4n potts/2d/8n potts/3d/6n potts/3d/26n
#		Nz only included for 3d lattices
#		random option initializes spin values using random values
#		read option reads initial spin values from file = filename
# sweep_style   lat 12345 (mask yes/no) (strict yes/no) (kmc yes/no) (delt = time per sweep or KMC threshold time, default 1.0)
#  		lat = lattice2d lattice3d
#		kmc option requires that a solve_style command be provided
# solve_style   see documentation for solve styles (if not used with kmc sweep style, serial execution only)
# temperature	0.1 = temperature (units of energy)
# stats		dt = print stats every dt time units
# dump		dt file = print snapshot to file every dt time units
# run	 	t = run for t time units

# Run potts/2d/8n with sweeping, parallel kmc and serial kmc

app_style	potts/2d/8n 100 100 100 12345
sweep_style     lattice2d 12345 strict no mask no delt 1.0e-2
temperature	0.2
stats           0.01
diag_style	energy2d

run		0.1

clear

app_style	potts/2d/8n 100 100 100 12345
sweep_style     lattice2d 12345 kmc yes delt 1.0e-2
solve_style     tree 12345
temperature	0.2
stats           0.01
diag_style	energy2d

run		0.1

clear

